						<p style="text-align:justify;"><p>The Korean government effectuated the Framework Act on Low Carbon Green Growth in April 2010, which was followed by the announcement of a comprehensive national CCS plan by the Presidential Committee on Green Growth three months later. Accordingly, a concrete plan to complete a local demonstration of CCS by 2010 has been carried out since then.</p>
						<p>In a position to play a key role in this regard, KNOC has launched a CCS task force to actively help the government implement its CCS policy and to develop high technologies that will lead the low carbon, green growth industry of the future. The main tasks of the unit include exploration of domestic CO2 storage sites and data interpretation; evaluation of domestic CO2 storage capacity; and research into drilling, injection, and post management systems.</p>
						<p><img src="../images/sub06/bullet_red_02.gif" width="8" height="9" alt="" />Explore underground CO2 storage sites and interpret data</p>
